Chelsea midfielder Nemanja Matic will miss the Capital One Cup final after being sent off against Burnley on Saturday.

The midfielder was shown a straight red after he pushed Ashley Barnes to the floor in retaliation for a terrible tackle by the Burnley man.

Barnes mistimed his challenge, catching Matic with his studs, but it was missed by referee Martin Atkinson.

